725925f-a.title: Queens: 159th Street - South Road
725925f-a.text:
1O5-43 159th Street, (formerly 103 Prospect Street), east
side, north of South Street, showing the S. Chapman house of 1873
which faces the last mentioned point and was still standing here
in 1931. In the background, east of same appears the steeyle
of an umdesignated church.
August 1924.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

725929f-a.title: Queens: 159th Street - South Road
725929f-a.text:
105-43 159th Street, east side, just north of South Road,
showing a frame dwelling, in all probability of colonial origin.
P. L. Sperr  April 6, 1932
